        "readme": "# mongodb-a\n\nFull-stack shopping cart app — Angular frontend, Nest.js backend, MongoDB.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend**: Angular (`client/`)\n- **Backend**: Nest.js (`server/`)\n- **Database**: MongoDB (web Atlas)\n\n## Features\n\n- Carts and products stored separately\n- Single-page layout with 3 cards: Carts, Cart, Messages\n- Scrolling support\n\n## Running\n\n```bash\ncd server && npm run start:dev   # Nest.js API\ncd client && ng serve            # Angular app\n```\n",
        "aboutTxt": "has 2 parts : cliend and server\r\n- use web MongoDB\r\n- carts and products stored separatelly\r\n- has one page only, one route page\r\n- page contains 3 cards (Carts, Cart, Messages)\r\n- has scrolling\r\n\r\nclient: \"start\": \"ng serve\",\r\nserver: \r\n    \"start\": \"nest start\",\r\n    \"start:dev\": \"nest start --watch\",\r\n    \"start:debug\": \"nest start --debug --watch\",\r\n    \"start:prod\": \"node dist/main\",\r\n\r\nexport const routes: Routes = [\r\n  {path: '', redirectTo: 'carts', pathMatch: 'full'},\r\n  {path: 'carts', component: CartsAndProducts},\r\n];\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
