        "readme": "# mysql\n\nFull-stack shopping cart app — Angular frontend, Node.js/TypeScript backend, MySQL.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend**: Angular (`client/`)\n- **Backend**: Node.js + TypeScript (`server/`)\n- **Database**: MySQL (local)\n\n## Features\n\n- Single-page layout with 3 cards: Carts, Cart, Messages\n\n## Running\n\n```bash\ncd server && npm run start   # Node.js API (tsc + node)\ncd client && ng serve        # Angular app\n```\n\nRequires local MySQL database.\n",
        "aboutTxt": "has 2 parts : cliend and server\r\n- use local MySQL DB\r\n- has one page only, one route page\r\n- page contains 3 cards (Carts, Cart, Messages)\r\n\r\nclient: \"start\": \"ng serve\",\r\nserver: \r\n    \"build\": \"tsc\",\r\n    \"dev\": \"node ./build/server.js\",\r\n    \"start\": \"tsc && npm run dev\"\r\n\r\nexport const routes: Routes = [\r\n  {path: '', redirectTo: 'carts', pathMatch: 'full'},\r\n  {path: 'carts', component: CartsAndProducts},\r\n];\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
