        "readme": "# BehaviorsubjectDemo\r\n\r\nThis project was generated with [Angular CLI](https://github.com/angular/angular-cli) version 17.0.3.\r\n\r\n## Development server\r\n\r\nRun `ng serve` for a dev server. Navigate to `http://localhost:4200/`. The application will automatically reload if you change any of the source files.\r\n\r\n## Code scaffolding\r\n\r\nRun `ng generate component component-name` to generate a new component. You can also use `ng generate directive|pipe|service|class|guard|interface|enum|module`.\r\n\r\n## Build\r\n\r\nRun `ng build` to build the project. The build artifacts will be stored in the `dist/` directory.\r\n\r\n## Running unit tests\r\n\r\nRun `ng test` to execute the unit tests via [Karma](https://karma-runner.github.io).\r\n\r\n## Running end-to-end tests\r\n\r\nRun `ng e2e` to execute the end-to-end tests via a platform of your choice. To use this command, you need to first add a package that implements end-to-end testing capabilities.\r\n\r\n## Further help\r\n\r\nTo get more help on the Angular CLI use `ng help` or go check out the [Angular CLI Overview and Command Reference](https://angular.io/cli) page.\r\n",
        "aboutTxt": null,
        "commentsTxt": "* * * Show update-quote & display-quote * * *\r\n\r\napp-update-quote :\r\n  <input type=\"text\" [(ngModel)]=\"quote\" placeholder=\"Write new quote\" />\r\n  <button (click)=\"submitHandler()\">Submit</button>\r\n\r\n  submitHandler(){\r\n   this.quoteService.updateQuote(this.quote);\r\n    this.quote='';\r\n  }\r\n\r\napp-display-quote :\r\n  <h2>{{currentQuote}}</h2>\r\n\r\n  currentQuote: string = '';\r\n\r\n  ngOnInit(): void {\r\n    this.quoteService.currentQuote.subscribe(quote => this.currentQuote = quote);\r\n  }\r\n\r\nQuoteService :\r\n  qoute = new BehaviorSubject(\"Hello world\");\r\n  currentQuote = this.qoute.asObservable();\r\n\r\n\r\n  updateQuote(newQuote: string){\r\n    this.qoute.next(newQuote);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n\r\n* * * Show behavior-subject * * *\r\n\r\ndifferenc-behavior-subject-bservable works!\r\n* * * logs * * *\r\n\r\n* * BehaviorSubject * *\r\n* const beSubject = new BehaviorSubject('a')\r\n* beSubject.next('b')\r\n* beSubject.subscribe(value => {\r\nBehaviorSubject - Subscription received the value b\r\n* beSubject.next('c')\r\nBehaviorSubject - Subscription received the value c\r\n* beSubject.next('d')\r\nBehaviorSubject - Subscription received the value d\r\n\r\n* * Subject * *\r\n* const subject = new Subject()\r\n* subject.next('b')\r\n* subject.subscribe(value => {\r\n* subject.next('c')\r\nSubject - Subscription received the value c\r\n* subject.next('d')\r\nSubject - Subscription received the value d\r\n\r\n* * * logs2* * *\r\n\r\n* * * logs3* * *\r\n\r\n* * * of(1, 2, 3).pipe(map((x) => x * x)) :\r\n.subscribe((v) : v= 1\r\n.subscribe((v) : v= 4\r\n.subscribe((v) : v= 9\r\n* * * of(1, 2, 3).pipe(first()) :\r\n.subscribe((v) : v= 1\r\n\r\n* * * logs4* * *\r\n\r\n* const subject = new BehaviorSubject(123)\r\n* subject.subscribe((v) - s1\r\ns1-subcribe : 123\r\n* subject.subscribe((v) - s2\r\ns2-subcribe : 123\r\n* subject.next(456)\r\ns1-subcribe : 456\r\ns2-subcribe : 456\r\n* subject.subscribe((v) - s3\r\ns3-subcribe : 456\r\n* subject.next(789)\r\ns1-subcribe : 789\r\ns2-subcribe : 789\r\ns3-subcribe : 789\r\n\r\n* * * logs5* * *\r\n\r\n* const observable1 = interval(400)\r\n* const observable2 = interval(300)\r\n* const subscription = observable1.subscribe((x) =>\r\n* const childSubscription = observable2.subscribe((x) =>\r\n* subscription.add(childSubscription);\r\nchildSubscription-second: 0\r\nsubscription-first: 0\r\nchildSubscription-second: 1\r\nsubscription-first: 1\r\nchildSubscription-second: 2\r\n* setTimeout( - subscription.unsubscribe() - 1000\r\n\r\n\r\n* * * Difference Between BehaviorSubject and Observable * * *\r\n\r\nprivate myBehaviorSubject = new BehaviorSubject<string>('Initial Value');\r\n\r\n  currentValue: string = 'currentValue';\r\n  behaviorSubjectSubscriptionValue: string = 'behaviorSubjectSubscriptionValue';\r\n\r\n  ngOnInit() {\r\n    // Subscribe to the BehaviorSubject\r\n    this.myBehaviorSubject.subscribe(value => {\r\n      this.currentValue = value;\r\n    });\r\n\r\n  updateValue() {\r\n    // Update the value of the\r\n    // BehaviorSubject and Observable\r\n    const newValue = `New Value ${Math.floor(Math.random() * 100)}`;\r\n    this.myBehaviorSubject.next(newValue);\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  delayedSubscribeToBehaviorSubject() {\r\n    // Delayed subscription to BehaviorSubject\r\n    setTimeout(() => {\r\n      this.myBehaviorSubject.subscribe(value => {\r\n\r\n        // Update value for display in HTML\r\n        this.behaviorSubjectSubscriptionValue = value;\r\n      });\r\n    }, 1000); // Delayed subscription after 1 second\r\n  }\r\n\r\n\r\n  <p class=\"col\">Current Value: {{ currentValue }}</p>\r\n  <button class=\"btn btn-primary col\" (click)=\"updateValue()\">Update Value</button>\r\n  <button class=\"btn btn-primary col\" (click)=\"delayedSubscribeToBehaviorSubject()\">Subscribe to BehaviorSubject</button>\r\n\r\n* * *\r\n\r\n  myObservable =\r\n    new Observable<string>(observer => {\r\n      // No initial value, just an example\r\n      observer.next('Initial Value');\r\n      this.emitValue = () => observer.next(\r\n        `New Value ${Math.floor(Math.random() * 100)}`);\r\n    });\r\n  currentValue2: string = 'currentValue2';\r\n  observableSubscriptionValue: string = 'observableSubscriptionValue';\r\n\r\n  // Function to emit a new value\r\n  emitValue!: () => void;\r\n\r\n  ngOnInit() {\r\n    this.myObservable.subscribe({\r\n      next: (v) => {\r\n        console.info('next : v=', v);\r\n        this.currentValue2 = v\r\n      },\r\n      error: (e) => console.error(e),\r\n      complete: () => console.info('complete')\r\n    });\r\n\r\n  updateValue2() {\r\n    // Update the value of the Observable\r\n    this.emitValue();\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  delayedSubscribeToObservable() {\r\n    // Delayed subscription to Observable\r\n    setTimeout(() => {\r\n      this.myObservable.subscribe(value => {\r\n        // Update value for display in HTML\r\n        this.observableSubscriptionValue = value;\r\n      });\r\n    }, 1000); // Delayed subscription after 1 sec\r\n  }\r\n\r\n  <p class=\"col\">Current Value: {{ currentValue2 }}</p>\r\n  <button class=\"btn btn-primary col\" (click)=\"updateValue2()\">Update Value</button>\r\n  <button class=\"btn btn-primary col\" (click)=\"delayedSubscribeToObservable()\">Subscribe to Observable</button>\r\n\r\n* * *\r\n\r\n  currentValue3: number = 0;\r\n  subscription3!: Subscription;\r\n\r\n  ngOnInit() {\r\n    const observable3: Observable<number> = interval(1000).pipe(take(10)); // stop on number 9\r\n    this.subscription3 = observable3.subscribe(\r\n      (value) => this.currentValue3 = value,\r\n      (error) => console.error(error),\r\n      () => console.log('Observable completed')\r\n    );\r\n\r\n<p class=\"col\">Subscribing to Observable - currentValue3: {{ currentValue3}}</p>\r\n\r\n* * *\r\n\r\nobservable4: Observable<number> = interval(1000); // value increased each 1 sec\r\n\r\n<p class=\"col\">Async Operator - value: {{ observable4 | async }}</p>\r\n",
