            "readme": "# react-node-mysql-more-backend\n\nReact frontend paired with multiple Node.js backend implementations for the same MySQL CRUD API.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend**: React + TypeScript (`frontend/react-typescript-api-call/`)\n- **Backend variants** (`backend/`):\n  - `node-js-typescript-mysql-rest-api/` — TypeScript + MySQL\n  - `nodejs-express-mysql/` — Express.js + MySQL\n  - `nodejs-express-sequelize-mysql/` — Express.js + Sequelize + MySQL\n  - `typescript-orm-mysql/` — TypeScript ORM + MySQL\n- **Database**: MySQL\n\n## Purpose\n\nCompare different Node.js backend approaches (raw driver vs Sequelize vs TypeORM) with a shared React frontend.\n",
