            "readme": "# json-server-c\n\nAngular shopping cart app — single-page layout with pagination and scrolling.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- Angular 20\n- Bootstrap + ng-bootstrap\n- JSON Server (`db2.json`)\n- RxJS, Lodash\n- TypeScript\n- Playwright (e2e tests)\n\n## Features\n\n- Carts and products stored separately\n- Single route page with 3 cards: Carts, Cart, Messages\n- Pagination and scrolling\n\n## Running\n\n```bash\nnpm run server   # json-server --watch src/assets/db2.json\nng serve\n```\n",
            "aboutTxt": "db2.json - carts and products are stored separatelly\r\n- has one page only, one route page\r\n- page contains 3 cards (Carts, Cart, Messages)\r\n- implemented scrolling and pagination\r\n\r\n\"server\": \"json-server --watch src/assets/db.json\",\r\n\r\nexport const routes: Routes = [\r\n  {path: '', redirectTo: 'carts', pathMatch: 'full'},\r\n  {path: 'carts', component: CartsAndProducts},\r\n];\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
            "commentsTxt": null,
