        "readme": "# Expense Tracker — Flutter Learning Project\n\nA full-stack personal expense tracker built to learn Flutter. Part of a framework exploration series (SvelteKit → Flutter).\n\n## Screenshots\n\n![Home](screen-1.png) ![Add Expense](screen-2.png) ![Charts](screen-3.png) ![Categories](screen-4.png)\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|-------|-----------|\n| Frontend | Flutter (Dart) |\n| State management | Riverpod (AsyncNotifier, StateProvider) |\n| Navigation | GoRouter |\n| HTTP client | Dio |\n| Models | freezed + json_serializable |\n| Charts | fl_chart |\n| Backend | NestJS (Node.js) |\n| ORM | Prisma 5 |\n| Database | MySQL |\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nFlutter/\n├── app/                    # Flutter frontend\n│   └── lib/\n│       ├── main.dart\n│       ├── models/         # freezed models (Category, Expense)\n│       ├── services/       # Dio API services\n│       ├── providers/      # Riverpod providers\n│       ├── router/         # GoRouter config\n│       ├── screens/\n│       │   ├── home/           # Expense list + monthly total\n│       │   ├── expense_form/   # Add / Edit expense\n│       │   ├── categories/     # Category management\n│       │   └── charts/         # Pie chart + bar chart\n│       ├── theme/          # Light / dark theme\n│       └── widgets/        # Shared widgets (AsyncValueWidget, MonthSelector)\n│\n└── backend/                # NestJS backend\n    ├── src/\n    │   ├── expenses/       # CRUD + monthly summary endpoint\n    │   ├── categories/     # CRUD\n    │   └── prisma/         # PrismaService\n    └── prisma/\n        ├── schema.prisma   # Category + Expense models\n        └── seed.ts         # Sample data\n```\n\n## Features\n\n- Add, edit, delete expenses\n- Assign expenses to color-coded categories\n- Filter expenses by month\n- Monthly total summary\n- Pie chart — spending by category\n- Bar chart — daily spending\n- Dark / light mode toggle\n- Swipe to delete with confirmation\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- [Flutter SDK](https://docs.flutter.dev/get-started/install/windows)\n- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) v18+\n- MySQL running locally\n\n## Setup\n\n### 1. Database\n\nCreate the database in MySQL:\n\n```sql\nCREATE DATABASE expense_tracker2;\n```\n\n### 2. Backend\n\n```bash\ncd backend\n\n# Install dependencies\nnpm install\n\n# Configure database connection\n# Edit .env: DATABASE_URL=\"mysql://YOUR_USER:YOUR_PASSWORD@localhost:3306/expense_tracker2\"\n\n# Run migrations (creates tables)\nnpx prisma migrate dev --name init\n\n# Seed sample data\nnpx prisma db seed\n\n# Start dev server (port 3000)\nnpm run start:dev\n```\n\n### 3. Flutter App\n\n```bash\ncd app\n\n# Install packages\nflutter pub get\n\n# Generate freezed models\nflutter pub run build_runner build --delete-conflicting-outputs\n\n# Run in browser\nflutter run -d edge\n# or\nflutter run -d chrome\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|--------|----------|-------------|\n| GET | `/categories` | List all categories |\n| POST | `/categories` | Create category |\n| PATCH | `/categories/:id` | Update category |\n| DELETE | `/categories/:id` | Delete category |\n| GET | `/expenses?month=YYYY-MM` | List expenses (optional month filter) |\n| POST | `/expenses` | Create expense |\n| PATCH | `/expenses/:id` | Update expense |\n| DELETE | `/expenses/:id` | Delete expense |\n| GET | `/expenses/summary/:month` | Monthly totals by category |\n\n## Flutter Concepts Covered\n\n**Beginner**\n- Dart null safety, async/await, Futures\n- Stateless vs Stateful widgets\n- Core widgets: ListView, Card, AppBar, Scaffold, Form\n- TextFormField validation\n- DatePicker, DropdownButtonFormField\n- Navigation with GoRouter (named routes, path params, push vs go)\n\n**Intermediate**\n- Riverpod: `AsyncNotifier`, `StateProvider`, `FutureProvider`, `ConsumerWidget`\n- `AsyncValue` loading / error / data pattern\n- Dio service layer with interceptors\n- Immutable models with freezed + json_serializable\n- Extension methods on model classes\n- fl_chart: `PieChart`, `BarChart`\n- Material 3 theming with dark mode\n",
