        "readme": "# HR Tutorial App\n\nA full-stack HR management application built with NestJS, Next.js 15, React 19, and MySQL.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n- **Frontend:** Next.js 15, React 19, TypeScript, Tailwind CSS\n- **Backend:** NestJS, TypeScript, TypeORM\n- **Database:** MySQL\n\n## Features\n\n- **Departments** — CRUD with detail modal showing manager and department employees\n- **Jobs** — CRUD with detail modal showing employees per job\n- **Employees** — CRUD with detail modal showing salary history, chart, and filters\n- **Salaries** — CRUD with three modal views:\n  - Month Salaries — view/edit salaries by year/month/department\n  - Department Salaries — salary summary grouped by department with chart\n  - Job Salaries — salary summary grouped by job with chart\n\nAll list pages include column sorting and a dynamic filter panel.\n\n## Database Schema\n\n| Table       | Key Columns                                                        |\n|-------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------|\n| employees   | id, first_name, last_name, birth_date, gender, hire_date, department_id, job_id |\n| departments | id, name, manager_id                                               |\n| jobs        | id, name, min_salary, max_salary                                   |\n| salaries    | id, employee_id, month, year, salary                               |\n\nThe backend creates tables automatically on startup and seeds test data if the tables are empty.\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n- Node.js 18+\n- MySQL running locally\n  - Host: `localhost`\n  - User: `root`\n  - Password: *(empty)*\n  - Database: `hr_tutorial`\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### 1. Create the database\n\n```sql\nCREATE DATABASE IF NOT EXISTS hr_tutorial;\n```\n\n### 2. Install dependencies\n\n```bash\n# Backend\ncd backend && npm install\n\n# Frontend\ncd frontend && npm install\n```\n\n### 3. Run the app\n\nFrom the project root:\n\n```bash\n# Start backend (http://localhost:3001)\nnpm run backend\n\n# Start frontend (http://localhost:3000)\nnpm run frontend\n```\n\nOr start each in a separate terminal using the commands above.\n\n## Testing\n\nThe project has three layers of tests.\n\n### Unit Tests (backend)\n\nTest individual service methods in isolation using mock repositories — no database or HTTP server required.\n\n```bash\ncd backend\nnpm test              # run once\nnpm run test:watch    # watch mode\n```\n\nLocation: `backend/src/**/*.spec.ts` (e.g. `employees.service.spec.ts`)\n\nEach service has ~12–13 tests covering the happy path, not-found errors, and edge cases. Jest mocks the TypeORM repository so tests run instantly without any external dependencies.\n\n### Integration Tests (backend)\n\nTest the full HTTP request → controller → service → database flow using `supertest` against a real MySQL database (`hr_tutorial_test`).\n\n```bash\ncd backend\nnpm run test:integration\n```\n\nLocation: `backend/src/**/*.integration.spec.ts`\n\nThe test database is created automatically on first run. Tables are truncated before each test to ensure isolation. Tests run sequentially (`--runInBand`) to avoid race conditions with TypeORM's schema sync.\n\n> **Prerequisite:** MySQL must be running locally (same connection as the main app).\n\n### E2E Tests (frontend)\n\nTest the full application through a real browser using Playwright — clicking buttons, filling forms, and verifying the UI updates correctly.\n\n```bash\ncd frontend\nnpm run test:e2e         # run headless\nnpm run test:e2e:ui      # open Playwright UI (recommended for watching tests live)\nnpm run test:e2e:report  # open last HTML report\n```\n\nLocation: `frontend/e2e/*.spec.ts`\n\n> **Prerequisite:** Both servers must be running before starting E2E tests:\n> - Frontend on `http://localhost:3000`\n> - Backend on `http://localhost:3001`\n\nCovers navigation, CRUD flows for all four entities, validation errors, filter panels, and report modals.\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nhr-tutorial/\n├── backend/          # NestJS API server\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── modules/  # departments, employees, jobs, salaries\n│       └── main.ts\n├── frontend/         # Next.js app\n│   └── src/\n│       └── app/      # App Router pages\n└── package.json      # Root scripts\n```\n",
        "aboutTxt": null,
        "commentsTxt": null,
