        "readme": "# Shopping List\n\nA full-stack web application for managing a shopping list organized by shops. Products can be grouped per shop, reordered via drag-and-drop, and browsed in a unified view across all shops.\n\n## Tech Stack\n\n| Layer | Technology |\n|---|---|\n| Frontend | Angular 21, Bootstrap 5, Angular CDK |\n| Backend | Spring Boot 3.4, Spring Data JPA |\n| Database | MySQL |\n\n## Prerequisites\n\n### Docker (recommended)\n\n- [Docker Desktop](https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop/)\n\n### Local development\n\n- Node.js 18+\n- Java 21\n- MySQL running on `localhost:3306`\n\n## Getting Started\n\n### Docker\n\nThe easiest way to run the full stack — no local Node.js, Java, or MySQL required.\n\n```bash\ndocker compose up --build\n```\n\n| Service | URL |\n|---|---|\n| Frontend | http://localhost |\n| Backend API | http://localhost:8080/api |\n| MySQL | localhost:3306 |\n\nMySQL data is persisted in a named Docker volume (`mysql_data`) across restarts.\n\nTo stop and remove containers:\n```bash\ndocker compose down\n```\n\nTo also delete the database volume:\n```bash\ndocker compose down -v\n```\n\n### Local Development\n\n#### 1. Database\n\nThe database `shopping_list` is created automatically on first run. Default credentials expected by the backend:\n\n```\nhost: localhost:3306\nusername: root\npassword: admin\n```\n\nTo use different credentials, edit `backend/src/main/resources/application.yml`.\n\n#### 2. Backend\n\n```bash\ncd backend\nmvn spring-boot:run\n```\n\nRuns at `http://localhost:8080`.\n\n#### 3. Frontend\n\n```bash\ncd frontend\nnpm install\nnpm start\n```\n\nRuns at `http://localhost:4200`.\n\n## Features\n\n- **Shops** — create, edit, delete, and reorder shops via drag-and-drop\n- **Products** — manage products per shop with drag-and-drop reordering\n- **All Products** — unified table view of every product across all shops\n- **Search** — live client-side filtering across shops and products\n- **Dark / Light mode** — theme toggle persisted in `localStorage`\n\n## E2E Tests\n\nTests use [Playwright](https://playwright.dev) and mock all API calls — no backend required.\n\n```bash\ncd frontend\n\n# First time only\nnpx playwright install chromium\n\n# Run tests (starts dev server automatically)\nnpm run test:e2e\n\n# Interactive UI mode\nnpm run test:e2e:ui\n```\n\n## Project Structure\n\n```\nshopping-list/\n├── docker-compose.yml\n├── frontend/\n│   ├── Dockerfile\n│   ├── nginx.conf\n│   ├── e2e/                    # Playwright E2E tests\n│   ├── src/app/\n│   │   ├── core/               # Models and services\n│   │   └── features/\n│   │       ├── shops/          # Dashboard, shops panel, products panel\n│   │       └── all-products/   # All products table view\n│   └── playwright.config.ts\n└── backend/\n    ├── Dockerfile\n    └── src/main/java/com/example/shoppinglist/\n        ├── controller/\n        ├── service/\n        ├── repository/\n        ├── entity/\n        └── dto/\n```\n\n## API\n\nBase URL: `http://localhost:8080/api`\n\n| Method | Endpoint | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| GET | `/shops` | List all shops |\n| POST | `/shops` | Create a shop |\n| PUT | `/shops/{id}` | Update a shop |\n| DELETE | `/shops/{id}` | Delete a shop and its products |\n| PATCH | `/shops/reorder` | Persist shop order |\n| GET | `/products` | List all products |\n| GET | `/products/shop/{shopId}` | List products for a shop |\n| POST | `/products` | Create a product |\n| PUT | `/products/{id}` | Update a product |\n| DELETE | `/products/{id}` | Delete a product |\n| PATCH | `/products/reorder` | Persist product order |\n",
        "aboutTxt": "",
